body.raw:
# API Reference

Welcome to the DocuSign Agent Tools API reference. This section provides detailed documentation for all available operations.

## Available Operations

### [Envelope Operations](/api-reference/envelope-operations)
Core operations for working with DocuSign envelopes:
- Get envelope details
- List envelopes
- Track envelope status

### [Document Operations](/api-reference/document-operations)
Operations for working with documents:
- Preview documents
- Create signing sessions
- Send reminders

### [Template Operations](/api-reference/template-operations)
Operations for working with templates:
- List templates
- Preview templates
- Get template fields
- Create envelopes from templates

### [Custom Document Operations](/api-reference/custom-document-operations)
Operations for custom documents:
- Create custom envelopes
- Preview custom documents

## Error Handling

All operations follow a consistent error handling pattern:

```typescript
try {
  const result = await toolkit.someOperation();
  if (result.error) {
    // Handle operation-specific error
    console.error(result.error);
    return;
  }
  // Use the result
} catch (error) {
  // Handle unexpected errors
  console.error('Unexpected error:', error);
}
```

## TypeScript Support

All operations are fully typed with TypeScript. You can import types from the package:

```typescript
import type { 
  EnvelopeDetails,
  TemplateInfo,
  SigningSession,
  CustomDocument
} from '@docusign-agent-tools/core';
```

# Template Operations

Operations for working with DocuSign templates, including listing templates, getting template details, and creating envelopes from templates.

## listTemplates

Lists available DocuSign templates.

### Returns

```typescript
{
  templates: Array<{
    templateId: string;
    name: string;
    description?: string;
  }>;
  error?: Error;
}
```

### Example Usage

```typescript
const { templates, error } = await toolkit.listTemplates();

if (error) {
  console.error('Failed to list templates:', error);
  return;
}

console.log('Available templates:', templates);
```

## previewTemplate

Retrieves detailed information about a DocuSign template.

### Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| templateId | `string` | The ID of the template to preview |

### Returns

```typescript
{
  template: {
    name: string;
    description?: string;
    roles: Array<{
      roleName: string;
      name?: string;
      email?: string;
    }>;
  };
  error?: Error;
}
```

### Example Usage

```typescript
const { template, error } = await toolkit.previewTemplate('template-123');

if (error) {
  console.error('Failed to preview template:', error);
  return;
}

console.log('Template details:', template);
```

## getTemplateFields

Retrieves the fields (tabs) available in a template for a specific role.

### Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| templateId | `string` | The ID of the template |
| roleName | `string` | The role to get fields for |

### Returns

```typescript
{
  fields: Array<{
    type: 'text' | 'number' | 'date' | 'signHere';
    label: string;
    value?: string;
    documentId: string;
    pageNumber: number;
    xPosition: number;
    yPosition: number;
  }>;
  error?: Error;
}
```

### Example Usage

```typescript
const { fields, error } = await toolkit.getTemplateFields({
  templateId: 'template-123',
  roleName: 'Signer 1'
});

if (error) {
  console.error('Failed to get template fields:', error);
  return;
}

console.log('Template fields:', fields);
```

## createEnvelopeFromTemplate

Creates a new envelope using a DocuSign template.

### Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| templateId | `string` | The ID of the template to use |
| emailSubject | `string` | Subject line for the email |
| emailBlurb | `string` | Message in the email body |
| recipients | `Array<{ roleName: string; name: string; email: string }>` | Recipients to assign to template roles |

### Returns

```typescript
{
  envelopeId: string;
  error?: Error;
}
```

### Example Usage

```typescript
const { envelopeId, error } = await toolkit.createEnvelopeFromTemplate({
  templateId: 'template-123',
  emailSubject: 'Please sign this document',
  emailBlurb: 'Please review and sign this document.',
  recipients: [
    {
      roleName: 'Signer 1',
      name: 'John Doe',
      email: 'john@example.com'
    }
  ]
});

if (error) {
  console.error('Failed to create envelope:', error);
  return;
}

console.log('Created envelope:', envelopeId);
```

